@ENDNODE
@NODE history "History of this program"

Version 1.0   - First public release.

Version 1.1   - Now displays a different pre-prompt line if all bulletins
                have been read.
              - Fixed a bug that wouldn't clear the attached file if you
                pressed [RETURN] instead of 'Y'.
              - Fixed a bug which would crash the machine if you attemped
                to download an attached file on a local port.
              - Made note of colour capabilities in feature list!
              - Now prints all bulletin slots, leaving them blank if no
                bulletin has been installed there.

Version 1.2   - Set maximum length of attached file specification to 69
                characters.
              - Can now run an optional command for each bulletin.
              - Now has 4 different types of forced reading delay messages.
              - Now asks before updating the 'Date Posted' field.
              - Can now set a range of access level people need to view
                bulletin.

Version 1.3   - Now also reverses the bulletin letter of read bulletins.
              - Changed the way input the user is prompted to select a
                bulletin. Now [RETURN] is handled as a key without a
                corresponding bulletin letter until all bulletins have
                been read.
              - Changed the message sent when un-read bulletins remain. It's
                now a little more friendly.

@ENDNODE

